<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"pillar-text","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"var(\u002d\u002dwp\u002d\u002dpreset\u002d\u002dfont-size\u002d\u002dlg)"},"color":{"text":"var(\u002d\u002dwp\u002d\u002dpreset\u002d\u002dcolor\u002d\u002dc-ash)"}}} -->
<p class="pillar-text has-text-color" style="color:var(--wp--preset--color--c-ash);font-size:var(--wp--preset--font-size--lg)">Once, the Veil held firm — an invisible wall between the mortal realm and the Otherdark. Now it tears. Creatures seep through the wounds. Magic bleeds unpredictably. Some say the Veil is not a barrier but a living thing, and it is dying.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></article>
<!-- /wp:group -->

