<!-- wp:heading {"level":3,"className":"pillar-title","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"var(\u002d\u002dwp\u002d\u002dpreset\u002d\u002dfont-size\u002d\u002d2xl)","fontFamily":"var(\u002d\u002dfont-display)"},"color":{"text":"var(\u002d\u002dwp\u002d\u002dpreset\u002d\u002dcolor\u002d\u002dc-gold)"}}} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading pillar-title has-text-color" style="color:var(--wp--preset--color--c-gold);font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:var(--wp--preset--font-size--2xl)">The Five Dominions</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"pillar-text","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"var(\u002d\u002dwp\u002d\u002dpreset\u002d\u002dfont-size\u002d\u002dlg)"},"color":{"text":"var(\u002d\u002dwp\u002d\u002dpreset\u002d\u002dcolor\u002d\u002dc-ash)"}}} -->
<p class="pillar-text has-text-color" style="color:var(--wp--preset--color--c-ash);font-size:var(--wp--preset--font-size--lg)">Five great powers carve Eldermoor between them: the Ashen Throne, the Covenant of Bloom, the Iron Vow, the Pale Court, and the Wandering Flame. Each claims dominion. None can be trusted. Your allegiance — or betrayal — will reshape their borders.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></article>
<!-- /wp:group -->

